    <token name="@HELP@">
        <![CDATA[
    Documentation

        The tool executes a series of conversion jobs on a given mass spectra file.

        The jobs specify service, source and target attribute, meaning that the service will use the source attribute
        to determine the target attribute. For example, the job `PubChem: inchi -> smiles` uses PubChem to convert
        InChI to SMILES.

        The performance can be adjusted by specifying the order of jobs (Order-specific conversion jobs section), which
        can influence the result. Alternatively, jobs can also be selected without specifying the order
        (Random order conversion jobs section). Both approaches can be combined. If no jobs are specified,
        all possible jobs will be executed in (pseudo) random order.

        For detailed documentation of the tool see https://msmetaenhancer.readthedocs.io/.
    ]]>
    </token>

